px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DFVjlmgRCfQ/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">Miley Cyrus（@mileycyrus）共享的帖子</a></p></div></blockquote><p><script async src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script></p><p> “这正是我需要做的……我不为自己的生活感到羞耻。我不需要放手，”安德森说。</p><p>赛勒斯回答说：“在我的生活中，当我回头看，所有的错误，我不确定或不明白的事情时，我都为生活的每个时刻和人生的每个阶段都感到自豪。</p><p> “我不会回去改变任何东西。除了我穿的几件衣服。”</p><p>她说：“让其他人不高兴的事情不是让我不高兴。”当安德森告诉赛勒斯“你从错误中学习”时，后者回答：“你知道吗？那就是生活。”</p><div class="pmc-contextual-player" data-pmc-adm-ad-id="10140328"><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/golden-globes-2025-nominations-see-full-list-3820321">赛勒斯（Cyrus）的“美丽”（Beautiful）在2025年颁奖典礼上获得了最佳原创歌曲的金球奖提名</a>。这位歌手说，这是“一种荣誉”，这是一个点头，写道：“我继续为[安德森]扎根，看着她的光芒真是太有趣了。</p><p> “谢谢Gia Coppola邀请我成为您<em>宝石</em>的一部分。” </p></div><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="麦莉·赛勒斯（Miley Cyrus）和帕梅拉·安德森（Pamela Anderson）坐下来讨论他们的新电影《现在的剧院》" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/b_VvwOOq_3o?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> 2023年， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-reflects-on-upsetting-controversy-around-2008-vanity-fair-cover-3491659">赛勒斯（Cyrus）反映了她15岁那年2008年的<em>虚荣博览会</em>封面上的“令人沮丧的”争议</a>。</p><p>她说：“我的这张照片与我以泡沫胶的流行明星的形式完全相反，这就是如此令人沮丧。” “但是，实际上，非常聪明的选择现在可以从这些人那里回头。”</p><p> When the cover was first released, Cyrus issued a statement apologising for the photoshoot. In 2018, however, she marked the 10th anniversary of the image and walked back her apology. “I&#39;m not sorry…fuck you #10yearsago,” she wrote.</p><p> Elsewhere in 2023, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-admits-to-feeling-guilt-and-shame-over-past-controversies-3445729">Cyrus admitted that she had felt “guilt and shame” over the controversies earlier in her career</a> . “Now that I&#39;m an adult, I realise how harshly I was judged,” she said.</p><p> The artist faced particular scrutiny in her early 20s when promoting her 2013 album &#39;Bangerz&#39;, which was seen as an attempt to radically shake off her Disney star image. She infamously twerked against <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robin-thicke">Robin Thicke</a> at that year&#39;s VMAs, and appeared naked on a demolition ball in the video for her hit single &#39;Wrecking Ball&#39;.</p><p> In other news, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-opens-up-about-her-new-era-and-looking-forward-to-starting-over-again-3825014">Cyrus teased her next era in late 2024, and expressed her excitement for “starting over again”</a> . She previously <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-working-on-pink-floyd-inspired-new-album-something-beautiful-but-more-glamorous-and-filled-with-pop-culture-3814522">revealed that her next studio album had been inspired by Pink Floyd&#39;s &#39;The Wall&#39;</a> , but described it as being “more glamorous and filled with pop culture”.</p><p> Last year saw the pop star win her first two <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/grammys">Grammy</a> awards, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-gives-first-televised-performance-of-flowers-at-2024-grammys-3582225">picking up Best Pop Solo Performance</a> and Record Of The Year for &#39;Flowers&#39;.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-on-being-so-proud-of-past-mistakes-and-what-she-would-change-3832536">Miley Cyrus on being “so proud” of past “mistakes” and what she would change</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
